articles.mainIdea: Mexican Stocks Hammer Wall Street As Peso Notches Best Year Since 1993
articles.summary: Benzinga: Mexican Stocks Hammer Wall Street As Peso Notches Best Year Since 1993. Mexican financial assets are closing out one of their strongest years in decades, stunning global investors and decisively outperforming Wall Street benchmarks. A synchronized rally in equities and the Mexican peso has erased early fears that renewed U.S. protectionist rhetoric under President Donald Trump would derail Mexico's markets. Instead, 2025 has turned into a historic year for Mexican assets.
